D001 M001 planning scope=product-identity decision=How far the ClaudeMeter to Pinemeter rename should go in M001 choice=Perform a comprehensive product and internal identity rename to Pinemeter wherever feasible, including project, scheme, target, source symbols, tests, docs/site, metadata, and user-facing copy. revisable=Yes, if execution finds a genuinely risky rename surface that requires explicit user approval.
D002 M001 planning scope=credential-architecture decision=Whether M001 should implement durable credential acquisition choice=M001 inventories and reviews credential/session handling, while M002 owns implementation of durable app-owned credential acquisition and persistence. revisable=Yes, if execution discovers an immediate low-risk security fix required in M001.
D003 M001 planning scope=architecture-review decision=How to use Opus for the architecture review choice=Attempt an Opus subprocess or advisor review if available, but produce a local ranked architecture review baseline if quota prevents Opus use. revisable=Yes, if Opus becomes available during execution.
D004 M001 planning scope=git-history decision=Whether M001 may squash or rewrite git history choice=M001 may prepare a non-destructive git history squash and open-source hygiene plan, but must not rewrite history or push remotely without fresh explicit confirmation. revisable=No for automatic execution; the user can explicitly approve a later destructive action.
D005 M001 planning scope=milestone-sequencing decision=How to sequence the broader Pinemeter ownership vision choice=Use M001 for ownership, safety, reviews, and cleanup; M002 for durable credential acquisition; M003 for provider-aware workflows; M004 for Gemini monitoring; and M005 for public open-source polish. revisable=Yes, after each milestone reassessment.
